  <!-- §1 INTRODUCTION -->
  <section class="content-section" id="sec-intro" data-checkpoint="0">
    <div class="sec-label">§ 01 — Overview</div>
    <h2>What Is Logo Design?</h2>
    <p>In the realm of visual communication and brand representation, few elements hold as much significance and power as the logo. A succinct symbol or emblem — often no larger than a few inches — the logo encapsulates the very essence of a brand, distilling its identity, values, and aspirations into a single image.</p>
    <p>From the iconic swoosh of Nike to the golden arches of McDonald's, logos have become ingrained in our collective consciousness, serving as the visual shorthand for some of the world's most recognizable companies and organizations.</p>
    <div class="callout">Logo design is not merely about crafting an attractive graphic. It is about crafting a visual representation that resonates with target audiences, communicates the brand's message effectively, and withstands the test of time.</div>
    <p>At its core, logo making is a journey of discovery. Designers delve deep into the brand's identity, values, and target audience to unearth visual elements that best encapsulate its essence. This process begins with extensive research and brainstorming — analyzing market trends, studying competitor logos, and exploring design styles to identify the unique visual language that will set the brand apart.</p>
    <p>From this foundation emerges the <strong>conceptualization phase</strong>, where ideas are sketched, refined, and iterated upon. Designers experiment with shapes, colors, typography, and symbolism, seeking the perfect balance between simplicity and complexity, tradition and innovation. Every element is carefully considered — from the curvature of a line to the spacing between letters.</p>
    <p>A well-crafted logo not only captures the essence of a brand but also invites interpretation, sparking curiosity and engagement. It becomes a visual anchor, fostering brand recognition, loyalty, and trust across diverse demographics and cultures.</p>
    <p>In today's digital age, a well-designed logo can transcend cultural and linguistic barriers, communicating the essence of a brand in an instant and leaving a lasting impression on consumers across the globe.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"><span>brand identity</span></div>

  <!-- §2 BRAND NAME -->
  <section class="content-section" id="sec-brandname" data-checkpoint="1">
    <div class="sec-label">§ 02 — Brand Name</div>
    <h2>Establishing Your Brand Name</h2>
    <p>Consider brainstorming a name that perfectly encapsulates your business. Aim for something <strong>catchy and memorable</strong>. Prioritize simplicity to ensure ease of recall. It is crucial to contemplate the brand name <em>before</em> finalizing the color palette, as it lays the foundation for the brand's identity and influences all aspects of its visual presentation.</p>

    <h3>Why Brand Name Comes First</h3>
    <p>Before diving into the intricacies of color selection, it is paramount to establish a strong foundation by defining the brand's identity through its name. The brand name serves as the cornerstone of its identity — encapsulating its essence, values, and positioning in the market.</p>
    <p>Once the brand name is established, it serves as a guiding beacon for subsequent branding decisions, including the choice of color palette. The name sets the tone and personality of the brand, influencing the emotions and perceptions it evokes in consumers.</p>

    <div class="color-grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(240px,1fr));">
      <div style="background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);padding:1.25rem;">
        <div style="font-family:'Syne',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">✦ Example: Sophisticated Brand</div>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem;margin:0;color:var(--muted);">A name conveying elegance calls for a palette featuring subdued tones and neutral hues — reinforcing perceptions of refinement and luxury.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);padding:1.25rem;">
        <div style="font-family:'Syne',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent2);font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">✦ Example: Energetic Brand</div>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem;margin:0;color:var(--muted);">A name conveying energy and excitement calls for bold, vibrant colors to amplify the message and capture consumers' attention immediately.</p>
